    "first-week-of-class": {
      "title": "First Week of Class, Pitt 2016",
      "content"	 : "First week of class has started. I have a pretty easy way of it this semester. There‚Äôs a CS class which is all web dev, and an InfoSci class that is design, basics, and some programming.In our web dev class, Matt is a strange and weirdly funny guy. His Google slide deck intro was:  Welcome to the Interwebs.I‚Äôm your host, Matt Bowytz.He also had a reference to Pittsburgh vernacular when he said:  Policies n‚ÄôatWhich I loved.No ES6 in Web DevUnfortunately, I think Matt doesn‚Äôt like ES6 or he doesn‚Äôt want to teach it. Whatever the case, it makes me sad but I understand it.We have a majority of seasoned programming vets in our class and some intermediates, like myself. I debated whether or not to change the name of this blog as I am no longer a newbie. Decided against it‚Äî this is what my blog is known by. It has been this name for almost two years. I‚Äôm sticking with it, for now.Anyway, we have a good amount of people familiar with web dev. There are some who have never coded before in their lives but that is rare.There are old heads like me in the class, too. That‚Äôs pretty damn cool.First CS ProjectWe will be building up to an e-commerce or some other site, whatever you want. Part one is making the bones of the site and Part 2 is finishing it off.I wanted to make my contacts app for this project but decided to go with the e-commerce site instead. First it will be HTML and CSS with CSS animations and then I‚Äôll up my game with JavaScript and jQuery.InfoSci Is Pretty Good, TooBob Perkoski is pretty darn funny and a true Pittsburgher, what with that accent, n‚Äôat.The classroom must be new‚Äî it‚Äôs huge and when I sat my black backpack down on the table it had newly sawed sawdust on it.We learned about UI design our first day of class. We also got thrown into a group project that same day.Group ProjectsI understand the need to show us what it will be like in teams in the workplace. And I understand that there are personalities in every team. Working through that? I don‚Äôt know.There‚Äôs a guy who wants to put all the things in the music app we are designing. Most of us 1 have advised against all these features. He is talking about building the thing himself, even though we don‚Äôt have to code anything. There‚Äôs even a Google Doc with the title: B code example in our folder.I don‚Äôt know how to deal with people like this, who are as equally headstrong, opinionated, and as arrogant as I am. It‚Äôs weird to see parts of yourself in other people.ThoughtsThis should be a 4.0 semester all the way. Bob admitted to how easy InfoSci 0010 is. I guarantee you I will get an A there.So far the first week of class is off to a fast start.Here is my Project 1 Proposal in a gist. Let me know what you think!https://gist.github.com/twhite96/88882d73339e79583705fe9484846a64¬†First week of class has started. I have a pretty easy way of it this semester. There‚Äôs a CS class which is all web dev, and an InfoSci class that is design, basics, and some programming.In our web dev class, Matt is a strange and weirdly funny guy. His Google slide deck intro was:  Welcome to the Interwebs.I‚Äôm your host, Matt Bowytz.He also had a reference to Pittsburgh vernacular when he said:  Policies n‚ÄôatWhich I loved.No ES6 in Web DevUnfortunately, I think Matt doesn‚Äôt like ES6 or he doesn‚Äôt want to teach it. Whatever the case, it makes me sad but I understand it.We have a majority of seasoned programming vets in our class and some intermediates, like myself. I debated whether or not to change the name of this blog as I am no longer a newbie. Decided against it‚Äî this is what my blog is known by. It has been this name for almost two years. I‚Äôm sticking with it, for now.Anyway, we have a good amount of people familiar with web dev. There are some who have never coded before in their lives but that is rare.There are old heads like me in the class, too. That‚Äôs pretty damn cool.First CS ProjectWe will be building up to an e-commerce or some other site, whatever you want. Part one is making the bones of the site and Part 2 is finishing it off.I wanted to make my contacts app for this project but decided to go with the e-commerce site instead. First it will be HTML and CSS with CSS animations and then I‚Äôll up my game with JavaScript and jQuery.InfoSci Is Pretty Good, TooBob Perkoski is pretty darn funny and a true Pittsburgher, what with that accent, n‚Äôat.The classroom must be new‚Äî it‚Äôs huge and when I sat my black backpack down on the table it had newly sawed sawdust on it.We learned about UI design our first day of class. We also got thrown into a group project that same day.Group ProjectsI understand the need to show us what it will be like in teams in the workplace. And I understand that there are personalities in every team. Working through that? I don‚Äôt know.There‚Äôs a guy who wants to put all the things in the music app we are designing. Most of us 1 have advised against all these features. He is talking about building the thing himself, even though we don‚Äôt have to code anything. There‚Äôs even a Google Doc with the title: B code example in our folder.I don‚Äôt know how to deal with people like this, who are as equally headstrong, opinionated, and as arrogant as I am. It‚Äôs weird to see parts of yourself in other people.ThoughtsThis should be a 4.0 semester all the way. Bob admitted to how easy InfoSci 0010 is. I guarantee you I will get an A there.So far the first week of class is off to a fast start.Here is my Project 1 Proposal in a gist. Let me know what you think!https://gist.github.com/twhite96/88882d73339e79583705fe9484846a64¬†            The 4 out of 7 of us participating, anyway¬†&amp;#8617;¬†&amp;#8617;2      ",
