ogle, Ask methodology they implement is a pretty important skill for any developer, junior or otherwise.I‚Äôve gone into the CodePen challenges quite ready for them, even though they‚Äôve been pretty simple so far, not really requiring any JavaScript at all 2. I know they‚Äôll get more difficult but I feel like out of Treehouse and Free Code Camp, Free Code Camp prepares you much better. I use Treehouse to shore up some knowledge and Free Code Camp to become better.My PlanMy plan is to remember what I‚Äôve been taught. I look at a thing like my contacts app and get overwhelmed. This can be avoided by looking at a small bit of functionality, brainstorming it with a mind map, listing things to do in TaskPaper, and then writing pseudocode to flesh it out, followed by actually source code implementation. There‚Äôs devdocs.io for online documentation, much like Dash Docs that won‚Äôt nag you and isn‚Äôt just Mac only. Kapeli has a fork of Dash for Windows you can find on his website. ‚Ü©Ô∏é Though I did add jQuery to the tribute page just to look like I knew what I was doing. Ha. ‚Ü©Ô∏é",
