    "first-java-program": {
      "title": "First Java Program and My Side Project",
      "content"	 : "My First Java ProgramI breezed through my first Java project with relative ease and little help. I can thank the year of struggling with things like Python and JavaScript for that level of comfort. I did need help with Operator Precedence and I probably will still need help with it in the interim. I also reached out to Stack Overflow for an answer: how do you escape and % sign in a format string? I knew  plus a letter escapes a lot of line breaks and characters but it doesn‚Äôt escape a % sign in a format string. So how do you escape a % sign? With 2 % signs. Interesting.I got to experience the thrill of debugging something myself. That feeling was satisfying. I am learning.So what does my first Java program look like? Well, because of the requirements, the code is really verbose. I don‚Äôt think I could use a method call at all to sort of DRY it out. I may be able to do that down the road./* Author name: Tiffany WhiteThis is a budget calculatorCreated date: September 22, 2015Last modified date: September 24, 2015*/// This line imports the Scanner class to the documentimport java.util.Scanner;public class P1A5_White{ public static void main(String[] args) {    // This line declares a scanner variable that will be used to get user input    Scanner keyboard = new Scanner(System.in);    // This line prints text to the screen    System.out.println(&amp;amp;quot;Welcome to Budget Calculator by Tiffany White. It will calculate your income and expenses.&amp;amp;quot;);    // The lines like these print instructions to the screen and then get user input    System.out.print(&amp;amp;quot;Enter your name.&amp;amp;quot;);    String name = keyboard.nextLine();    System.out.print(&amp;amp;quot;Enter your hourly rate.&amp;amp;quot;);    double hourlyRate = keyboard.nextDouble();    System.out.print(&amp;amp;quot;Enter your regular hours worked.&amp;amp;quot;);    int regularHoursWorked = keyboard.nextInt();    System.out.print(&amp;amp;quot;Enter your overtime hours worked.&amp;amp;quot;);    double overtimeHoursWorked = keyboard.nextDouble();    // Clears keyboard buffer    keyboard.nextLine();    System.out.print(&amp;amp;quot;Enter your rent.&amp;amp;quot;);    double rent = keyboard.nextDouble();    System.out.print(&amp;amp;quot;Enter your electric bill amount.&amp;amp;quot;);    double elecBill = keyboard.nextDouble();    System.out.print(&amp;amp;quot;Enter the amount of your water bill.&amp;amp;quot;);    double waterBill = keyboard.nextDouble();    // Clears keyboard buffer    keyboard.nextLine();    System.out.print(&amp;amp;quot;Enter the amount of your sewage bill.&amp;amp;quot;);    double sewBill = keyboard.nextDouble();    System.out.print(&amp;amp;quot;Enter the amount of your gas bill.&amp;amp;quot;);    double gasBill = keyboard.nextDouble();    System.out.print(&amp;amp;quot;Enter the amount of your food budget.&amp;amp;quot;);    double foodBudget = keyboard.nextDouble();    // Clears keyboard buffer    keyboard.nextLine();    System.out.print(&amp;amp;quot;Enter the amount of your entertainment expenses.&amp;amp;quot;);    double entertainment = keyboard.nextDouble();    System.out.print(&amp;amp;quot;Enter the amount of your car expenses.&amp;amp;quot;);    double carExpenses = keyboard.nextDouble();    // Clears keyboard buffer    keyboard.nextLine();    // This line calculates the user&#39;s gross pay    double grossPay = (regularHoursWorked + overtimeHoursWorked) * hourlyRate;    //This format string prints out the reults of the grossPay calculation and returns a new line    System.out.printf(&amp;amp;quot;Your gross pay is &amp;amp;quot; + &amp;amp;quot;%.2f%%, grossPay);    // This line calculates expenses/deductions    double deductions = (rent + elecBill + waterBill + sewBill + gasBill    + foodBudget + entertainment + carExpenses);    // This line declares variables in the double primitive data type    double rentPercentage, elecBillPercentage, waterBillPercentage, sewBillPercentage,    gasBillPercentage, foodBudgetPercentage, entertainmentPercentage, carExpensesPercentage;    /* The following lines of code calculate the percentages of each deduction against    the user&#39;s gross pay and prints out the results to the console, returning a new line    */    rentPercentage = (rent * 100) / grossPay;System.out.printf(&amp;amp;quot;The amount of your gross pay that goes to rent is %.2f%%.n&amp;amp;quot;, rentPercentage);elecBillPercentage = (elecBill * 100) / grossPay;    System.out.printf(&amp;amp;quot;The amount of your gross pay that goes to your electric bill is %.2f%%.n&amp;amp;quot;, elecBillPercentage);    waterBillPercentage = (waterBill * 100) / grossPay;    System.out.printf(&amp;amp;quot;The amount of your gross pay that goes to your water bill is %.2f%%.n&amp;amp;quot;, waterBillPercentage);    sewBillPercentage = (sewBill * 100) / grossPay;    System.out.printf(&amp;amp;quot;The amount of your gross pay that goes to sewage is %.2f%%.n&amp;amp;quot;, sewBillPercentage);    gasBillPercentage = (gasBill * 100) / grossPay;    System.out.printf(&amp;amp;quot;The amount of your gross pay that goes to gas is %.2f%%.n&amp;amp;quot;, gasBillPercentage);    foodBudgetPercentage = (foodBudget * 100) / grossPay;    System.out.printf(&amp;amp;quot;The amount of your gross pay that goes to food is %.2f%%.n&amp;amp;quot;, foodBudgetPercentage);    entertainmentPercentage = (entertainment * 100) / grossPay;    System.out.printf(&amp;amp;quot;The amount of your gross pay that goes to entertainment is %.2f%%.n&amp;amp;quot;, entertainmentPercentage);    carExpensesPercentage = (carExpenses * 100) / grossPay;    System.out.printf(&amp;amp;quot;The amount of your gross pay that goes to your car is %.2f%%.n&amp;amp;quot;, carExpensesPercentage);    // This line calculates net pay after deductions are subtracted from the gross pay    double netPay = (grossPay - deductions);    // This format string prints out the net pay to the console and returns a new line    System.out.printf(&amp;amp;quot;Your net pay after deductions is $&amp;amp;quot; + &amp;amp;quot;%.2f.n&amp;amp;quot;, netPay);  }/* Author name: Tiffany WhiteThis is a budget calculatorCreated date: September 22, 2015Last modified date: September 24, 2015*/// This line imports the Scanner class to the documentimport java.util.Scanner;public class P1A5_White{ public static void main(String[] args) {    // This line declares a scanner variable that will be used to get user input    Scanner keyboard = new Scanner(System.in);    // This line prints text to the screen    System.out.println(&amp;amp;quot;Welcome to Budget Calculator by Tiffany White. It will calculate your income and expenses.&amp;amp;quot;);    // The lines like these print instructions to the screen and then get user input    System.out.print(&amp;amp;quot;Enter your name.&amp;amp;quot;);    String name = keyboard.nextLine();    System.out.print(&amp;amp;quot;Enter your hourly rate.&amp;amp;quot;);    double hourlyRate = keyboard.nextDouble();    System.out.print(&amp;amp;quot;Enter your regular hours worked.&amp;amp;quot;);    int regularHoursWorked = keyboard.nextInt();    System.out.print(&amp;amp;quot;Enter your overtime hours worked.&amp;amp;quot;);    double overtimeHoursWorked = keyboard.nextDouble();    // Clears keyboard buffer    keyboard.nextLine();    System.out.print(&amp;amp;quot;Enter your rent.&amp;amp;quot;);    double rent = keyboard.nextDouble();    System.out.print(&amp;amp;quot;Enter your electric bill amount.&amp;amp;quot;);    double elecBill = keyboard.nextDouble();    System.out.print(&amp;amp;quot;Enter the amount of your water bill.&amp;amp;quot;);    double waterBill = keyboard.nextDouble();    // Clears keyboard buffer    keyboard.nextLine();    System.out.print(&amp;amp;quot;Enter the amount of your sewage bill.&amp;amp;quot;);    double sewBill = keyboard.nextDouble();    System.out.print(&amp;amp;quot;Enter the amount of your gas bill.&amp;amp;quot;);    double gasBill = keyboard.nextDouble();    System.out.print(&amp;amp;quot;Enter the amount of your food budget.&amp;amp;quot;);    double foodBudget = keyboard.nextDouble();    // Clears keyboard buffer    keyboard.nextLine();    System.out.print(&amp;amp;quot;Enter the amount of your entertainment expenses.&amp;amp;quot;);    double entertainment = keyboard.nextDouble();    System.out.print(&amp;amp;quot;Enter the amount of your car expenses.&amp;amp;quot;);    double carExpenses = keyboard.nextDouble();    // Clears keyboard buffer    keyboard.nextLine();    // This line calculates the user&#39;s gross pay    double grossPay = (regularHoursWorked + overtimeHoursWorked) * hourlyRate;    //This format string prints out the reults of the grossPay calculation and returns a new line    System.out.printf(&amp;amp;quot;Your gross pay is &amp;amp;quot; + &amp;amp;quot;%.2f%%, grossPay);    // This line calculates expenses/deductions    double deductions = (rent + elecBill + waterBill + sewBill + gasBill    + foodBudget + entertainment + carExpenses);    // This line declares variables in the double primitive data type    double rentPercentage, elecBillPercentage, waterBillPercentage, sewBillPercentage,    gasBillPercentage, foodBudgetPercentage, entertainmentPercentage, carExpensesPercentage;    /* The following lines of code calculate the percentages of each deduction against    the user&#39;s gross pay and prints out the results to the console, returning a new line    */    rentPercentage = (rent * 100) / grossPay;System.out.printf(&amp;amp;quot;The amount of your gross pay that goes to rent is %.2f%%.n&amp;amp;quot;, rentPercentage);elecBillPercentage = (elecBill * 100) / grossPay;    System.out.printf(&amp;amp;quot;The amount of your gross pay that goes to your electric bill is %.2f%%.n&amp;amp;quot;, elecBillPercentage);    waterBillPercentage = (waterBill * 100) / grossPay;    System.out.printf(&amp;amp;quot;The amount of your gross pay that goes to your water bill is %.2f%%.n&amp;amp;quot;, waterBillPercentage);    sewBillPercentage = (sewBill * 100) / grossPay;    System.out.printf(&amp;amp;quot;The amount of your gross pay that goes to sewage is %.2f%%.n&amp;amp;quot;, sewBillPercentage);    gasBillPercentage = (gasBill * 100) / grossPay;    System.out.printf(&amp;amp;quot;The amount of your gross pay that goes to gas is %.2f%%.n&amp;amp;quot;, gasBillPercentage);    foodBudgetPercentage = (foodBudget * 100) / grossPay;    System.out.printf(&amp;amp;quot;The amount of your gross pay that goes to food is %.2f%%.n&amp;amp;quot;, foodBudgetPercentage);    entertainmentPercentage = (entertainment * 100) / grossPay;    System.out.printf(&amp;amp;quot;The amount of your gross pay that goes to entertainment is %.2f%%.n&amp;amp;quot;, entertainmentPercentage);    carExpensesPercentage = (carExpenses * 100) / grossPay;    System.out.printf(&amp;amp;quot;The amount of your gross pay that goes to your car is %.2f%%.n&amp;amp;quot;, carExpensesPercentage);    // This line calculates net pay after deductions are subtracted from the gross pay    double netPay = (grossPay - deductions);    // This format string prints out the net pay to the console and returns a new line    System.out.printf(&amp;amp;quot;Your net pay after deductions is $&amp;amp;quot; + &amp;amp;quot;%.2f.n&amp;amp;quot;, netPay);  }}See what I mean by verbose? But we‚Äôre beginners so I guess she wants to make sure we know what we‚Äôre doing. ¬Ø&amp;#95;(„ÉÑ)_/¬ØMy Side ProjectSo I had the chance this week to work on my address book. I am looking for ways to use Google‚Äôs Contacts API and am in the process of looking for API courses or videos. I also want to write my own RESTful APIs eventually so I need to get cracking on the learning of that.I am only taking 6 credits so I have some in between time. It won‚Äôt be that way next fall as I try to get scholarships and with most scholarships, you have to be 12 credits to get them. It doesn‚Äôt bother me‚Äì mostly all my gen eds are completed so I can focus on Computer Science for the next two or three years.Anyway, I‚Äôve used some simple Bootstrap to set up a few of the pages. Here‚Äôs the static html code for the index page:&amp;amp;lt;html lang=&amp;amp;quot;en&amp;amp;quot;&amp;amp;gt;&amp;amp;lt;head&amp;amp;gt;    &amp;amp;lt;meta charset=&amp;amp;quot;UTF-8&amp;amp;quot;&amp;amp;gt;    &amp;amp;lt;!-- Latest compiled and minified CSS --&amp;amp;gt;    &amp;amp;lt;link rel=&amp;amp;quot;stylesheet&amp;amp;quot; href=&amp;amp;quot;https://maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/3.3.5/css/bootstrap.min.css&amp;amp;quot;&amp;amp;gt;    &amp;amp;lt;!-- Optional theme --&amp;amp;gt;    &amp;amp;lt;link rel=&amp;amp;quot;stylesheet&amp;amp;quot; href=&amp;amp;quot;https://maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/3.3.5/css/bootstrap-theme.min.css&amp;amp;quot;&amp;amp;gt;    &amp;amp;lt;!-- Latest compiled and minified JavaScript --&amp;amp;gt;    &amp;amp;lt;script src=&amp;amp;quot;https://maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/3.3.5/js/bootstrap.min.js&amp;amp;quot;&amp;amp;gt;&amp;amp;lt;/script&amp;amp;gt;    &amp;amp;lt;link rel=&amp;amp;quot;stylesheet&amp;amp;quot; type=&amp;amp;quot;text/css&amp;amp;quot; href=&amp;amp;quot;stylesheet.css&amp;amp;quot;&amp;amp;gt;&amp;amp;lt;/head&amp;amp;gt;&amp;amp;lt;body&amp;amp;gt;&amp;amp;lt;div class=&amp;amp;quot;navbar-header&amp;amp;quot;&amp;amp;gt;&amp;amp;lt;ul class=&amp;amp;quot;nav nav-tabs&amp;amp;quot;&amp;amp;gt;&amp;amp;lt;li role=&amp;amp;quot;presentation&amp;amp;quot; class=&amp;amp;quot;active&amp;amp;quot;&amp;amp;gt;&amp;amp;lt;a href=&amp;amp;quot;index.html&amp;amp;quot;&amp;amp;gt;Contacts&amp;amp;lt;/a&amp;amp;gt;&amp;amp;lt;/li&amp;amp;gt;&amp;amp;lt;li role=&amp;amp;quot;presentation&amp;amp;quot;&amp;amp;gt;&amp;amp;lt;a href=&amp;amp;quot;addContacts.html&amp;amp;quot;&amp;amp;gt;Add Contacts&amp;amp;lt;/a&amp;amp;gt;&amp;amp;lt;/li&amp;amp;gt;&amp;amp;lt;li role=&amp;amp;quot;presentation&amp;amp;quot;&amp;amp;gt;&amp;amp;lt;a href=&amp;amp;